The TPD8E003 device is a unidirectional Transient Voltage Suppressor (TVS) based Electrostatic Discharge (ESD) protection diode array. The TPD8E003 is rated to dissipate ESD strikes above the maximum level specified in the IEC 61000-4-2 international standard (Level 4). This device provides 8 channels of ESD protection in a space-saving WSON package. Typical applications for the TPD8E003 include Keypad, GPIO, resistive touchscreen, and low-speed memory interfaces. Also, see the TPD2E2U06 and TPD4E05U06 for 2- and 4-channel ESD protection solutions, respectively.
